TASK 2:
       Open your laptop or desktop (with power disconnected), locate the RAM slots, and take a clear photo of the installed RAM module. Reinstall the RAM module and verify that your system boots up successfully. Refer to your device manual or a trusted YouTube guide if unsure about RAM removal and installation steps.



1. Shut down the computer completely.
2. Unplug the power cable (and remove the battery if it's removable).
3. Press and hold the power button for 10–15 seconds to discharge residual power.
4. Open the case or RAM access panel according to your device manual.
5. Locate the RAM modules in their slots.
6. Take a clear photo of the installed RAM.
7. Release the retaining clips and carefully remove the RAM module.
8. Reinsert the module firmly into the same slot until the clips lock into place.
9. Close the case, reconnect power, and start the computer.
10. Confirm that the system boots normally and recognizes the installed memory.

